HEADWORD: Hussite
<hw>Huss"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld>
<def>A follower of John <xex>Huss</xex>, the Bohemian reformer, who was
adjudged a heretic and burnt alive in 1415.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

